  <reg:title>Spongy Moth Eradication Regulation</reg:title>
  <reg:amsincluded>[Last amended April 24, 2023 by B.C. Reg. 109/2023]</reg:amsincluded>
  <reg:regpitid>100_2022_pit</reg:regpitid>
  <reg:content>
    <bcl:section id="d1e19">
      <bcl:marginalnote>Definitions</bcl:marginalnote>
      <bcl:num>1</bcl:num>
      <bcl:text>In this regulation:</bcl:text>
      <bcl:definition id="d1e27">
        <bcl:text>
          <in:term>Btk</in:term> means an insecticide containing <in:em>Bacillus thuringiensis</in:em> var. <in:em>kurstaki</in:em> as its active ingredient;</bcl:text>
      </bcl:definition>
      <bcl:definition id="d1e34">
        <bcl:text>
          <in:term>buffer zone</in:term> means the area shown in grey surrounding a treatment zone on the map in the Schedule that relates to that treatment zone;</bcl:text>
      </bcl:definition>
      <bcl:definition id="d1e77">
        <bcl:text>
          <in:term>pesticide droplet monitoring card</in:term> means a card which is used to determine the number, density and size of droplets of pesticide spray deposited at a particular location;</bcl:text>
      </bcl:definition>
      <bcl:definition id="d1e42">
        <bcl:text>
          <in:term>spongy moth</in:term> means the following species of moth:</bcl:text>
        <bcl:paragraph id="d1e48">
          <bcl:num>a</bcl:num>
          <bcl:text>
            <in:em>Lymantria albescens</in:em>;</bcl:text>
        </bcl:paragraph>
        <bcl:paragraph id="d1e55">
          <bcl:num>b</bcl:num>
          <bcl:text>
            <in:em>Lymantria dispar</in:em>;</bcl:text>
        </bcl:paragraph>
        <bcl:paragraph id="d1e62">
          <bcl:num>c</bcl:num>
          <bcl:text>
            <in:em>Lymantria dispar dispar</in:em>;</bcl:text>
        </bcl:paragraph>
        <bcl:paragraph id="d1e69">
          <bcl:num>d</bcl:num>
          <bcl:text>
            <in:em>Lymantria umbrosa</in:em>;</bcl:text>
        </bcl:paragraph>
      </bcl:definition>
      <bcl:definition id="d1e84">
        <bcl:text>
          <in:term>treatment period</in:term> means the period that begins April 1 and ends October 31;</bcl:text>
      </bcl:definition>
      <bcl:definition id="d1e91">
        <bcl:text>
          <in:term>treatment zone</in:term> means a specified area outlined in heavy black on a map in the Schedule.</bcl:text>
      </bcl:definition>
      <bcl:hnote>[am. B.C. Reg. 109/2023, s. 2.]</bcl:hnote>
    </bcl:section>
    <bcl:section id="d1e99">
      <bcl:marginalnote>Powers of inspectors</bcl:marginalnote>
      <bcl:num>2</bcl:num>
      <bcl:subsection id="d1e105">
        <bcl:num>1</bcl:num>
        <bcl:text>Subject to the limits set out in section 3, an inspector has the following powers:</bcl:text>
        <bcl:paragraph id="d1e111">
          <bcl:num>a</bcl:num>
          <bcl:text>to undertake treatment within a treatment zone by applying Btk, using an aerial or ground spray;</bcl:text>
        </bcl:paragraph>
        <bcl:paragraph id="d1e118">
          <bcl:num>b</bcl:num>
          <bcl:text>to enter on land in a treatment zone to do any of the following:</bcl:text>
          <bcl:subparagraph id="d1e124">
            <bcl:num>i</bcl:num>
            <bcl:text>search for and remove spongy moth eggs;</bcl:text>
          </bcl:subparagraph>
          <bcl:subparagraph id="d1e131">
            <bcl:num>ii</bcl:num>
            <bcl:text>search for spongy moths;</bcl:text>
          </bcl:subparagraph>
          <bcl:subparagraph id="d1e138">
            <bcl:num>iii</bcl:num>
            <bcl:text>set or retrieve traps for spongy moths;</bcl:text>
          </bcl:subparagraph>
        </bcl:paragraph>
        <bcl:paragraph id="d1e146">
          <bcl:num>c</bcl:num>
          <bcl:text>to enter on land in a treatment zone or buffer zone to set or retrieve pesticide droplet monitoring cards.</bcl:text>
        </bcl:paragraph>
      </bcl:subsection>
      <bcl:subsection id="d1e154">
        <bcl:num>2</bcl:num>
        <bcl:text>For the purposes of subsection (1) (a), a treatment may consist of the application of Btk over multiple days if, due to mechanical, meteorological or any other reason, Btk cannot be applied throughout the treatment zone in a single day.</bcl:text>
      </bcl:subsection>
      <bcl:subsection id="d1e161">
        <bcl:num>3</bcl:num>
        <bcl:text>Nothing in subsection (1) (a) limits an authorization granted under the <bcl:link resource="leg" xlink:href="/legislation/03058_01" xlink:type="locator"><in:doc>Integrated Pest Management Act</in:doc></bcl:link> for overspray or drift from treatment to pass into the buffer zone.</bcl:text>
      </bcl:subsection>
      <bcl:hnote>[am. B.C. Reg. 109/2023, s. 3.]</bcl:hnote>
    </bcl:section>
    <bcl:section id="d1e169">
      <bcl:marginalnote>Limits on powers</bcl:marginalnote>
      <bcl:num>3</bcl:num>
      <bcl:text>An inspector may exercise powers under section 2 only as follows:</bcl:text>
      <bcl:paragraph id="d1e177">
        <bcl:num>a</bcl:num>
        <bcl:text>Btk may be applied in a treatment zone only during the treatment period;</bcl:text>
      </bcl:paragraph>
      <bcl:paragraph id="d1e184">
        <bcl:num>b</bcl:num>
        <bcl:text>no more than 4 treatments may be undertaken during the treatment period;</bcl:text>
      </bcl:paragraph>
      <bcl:paragraph id="d1e192">
        <bcl:num>c</bcl:num>
        <bcl:text>land in a treatment zone may be entered for a purpose set out in section 2 (1) (b) only during the treatment period;</bcl:text>
      </bcl:paragraph>
      <bcl:paragraph id="d1e199">
        <bcl:num>d</bcl:num>
        <bcl:text>land in a treatment zone or buffer zone may be entered for a purpose set out in section 2 (1) (c) only during the treatment period.</bcl:text>
      </bcl:paragraph>
    </bcl:section>
